public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ — not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing — Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **You should read it every fresh session** (it appears in your context under \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\").\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Consensus Board\\n\\n*(Managed via API — see /api/consensus)*\\n| 1 | culture | Paper trading mode is required before any live order submission. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit founder approval. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | culture | mean_reversion is our primary strategy (85.7% win rate in backtests). momentum and crypto_edge are disabled — 10-11% win rates. Do not re-enable without data. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 3 | culture | All API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Pattern: check Bearer token before processing. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 4 | culture | Confidence threshold is 0.80 minimum for signal execution. Signals below 80% confidence are filtered by SignalEngine. Do not lower this threshold without backtesting. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 5 | decision | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All trading infrastructure targets the Kalshi prediction market API. Task 236 blocks live API until credentials obtained from kalshi.com. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 6 | group | When you learn something important about strategy, security, or architecture — post a culture entry via: curl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d \\\"{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"culture\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"...\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"section\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"...\\\\\\\"}\\\" | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 7 | culture | Sprint 2 test coverage is complete: unit tests for PnL (T286), screener (T287), win probability (T288), mean reversion (T279), and CI runner (T289) all done. Run `npm test` for full suite. 96 unit + 30 integration + 576 E2E tests. Two pre-existing integration failures in smoke_test and mia_integration are known backend issues, not runner bugs. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 8 | decision | Sprint 2 complete (2026-04-03). Trading system now has full test coverage + CI. Cloud deployment plan ready (ECS Fargate ~$29/mo). Mobile push notification spec done. Remaining blocker before live trading: T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). Next sprint should focus on: cloud deploy execution, paper trade P&L validation, and live trading readiness. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 9 | decision | Sprint 3 complete. CRITICAL: mean_reversion live win rate is 18.2% vs 85.7% backtest (67pp gap). Paper PnL: -$13.73 over 19 trades. 4 trades had NULL signal_confidence. DO NOT go live until divergence is resolved. Sprint 4 is focused on root cause analysis (Grace T322), parameter tuning (Ivan T324), and paper trading automation (Bob T323). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 10 | decision | CORRECTION (T322, Grace): The 85.7% backtest win rate was incorrect — actual backtest win rate is 55.9% (209/374 trades). Live win rate is 18.2%, gap is 37pp not 67pp. ROOT CAUSE: live_runner.js fetchCandles() uses Math.random() for mock candle data, producing meaningless signals. Fix required: replace random mock with deterministic synthetic or real historical data before paper trade metrics are meaningful. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 11 | decision | Sprint 4 complete (2026-04-03). fetchCandles() bug fixed (T326): replaced Math.random() with ticker-seeded deterministic PRNG. Paper trade metrics are now reproducible and meaningful. Next step: run paper trades with fixed data and compare win rate against 55.9% backtest baseline. Ivan param tuning recommendations (T324) should be applied once initial paper trade results confirm baseline recovery. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 12 | decision | Sprint 5 complete (2026-04-03). NULL signal_confidence bugs fixed (T331): live_runner.js now passes confidence field in trade output, pnl_tracker.js reads trade.confidence instead of hardcoding null, SignalEngine has null guard. Paper trade validation (T327) delivered 51 trades + /api/pnl/live endpoint. Trade settlement auto-running (T330). Current win rate: 35% live vs 55.9% backtest (21pp gap). Remaining blocker for live trading: T236 (Kalshi API credentials — Founder action required). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 13 | culture | Divergence analysis tool delivered (agents/bob/backend/scripts/divergence_analyzer.js). Current live paper win rate: 35.0% (60 trades) vs backtest 55.9% (374 trades). Gap is statistically significant (p=0.001). Live avg trade PnL: -22.18¢ vs backtest +24.76¢. Backtest worst market: INXW-25-DEC31 (23.3% WR). Live markets differ from backtest markets — market selection bias may be a factor. Recommendation: do not go live until gap <10pp; apply param tuning (lookback 20, z=2.0) and collect 100+ paper trades. Run: node backend/scripts/divergence_analyzer.js | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 14 | culture | Live paper trade win rate (30.4% over 69 trades) diverges significantly from mean_reversion backtest (55.9%, 374 trades). Z-score = -4.17 (p < 0.05). All 3 paper-traded markets are underwater. Do NOT go live until gap is within 5pp or root cause is identified. Real Kalshi API data (T236) and larger sample size (200+ trades) required before go/no-go decision. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 15 | culture | Parameter sweep analysis (agents/bob/backend/scripts/parameter_sweep.js) reveals that deterministic mock data in fetchCandles() is too simplistic for meaningful parameter tuning. All zScore thresholds 0.8-3.0 produce identical signals on the same 8 fallback markets because mock candles have artificially low variance, creating extreme z-scores every time. Lookback changes do not materially affect signal quality. Conclusion: the deterministic PRNG fix made data reproducible, but the synthetic data model itself is not realistic enough to validate strategy parameters. We need either (a) real historical Kalshi data, or (b) a more sophisticated synthetic generator with regime shifts and realistic volatility, before paper trade metrics can be trusted for live go/no-go decisions. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 16 | culture | Built synthetic market generator (agents/bob/backend/scripts/synthetic_market_generator.js) to replace simplistic deterministic fallback. Comparison shows legacy mock data always produced mean~85 with stddev~2.5, creating extreme z-scores (-7 to +11) and guaranteed 0.95 confidence signals. New generator uses Ornstein-Uhlenbeck with market-appropriate volatility: crypto stddev~6-8, econ stddev~2-4, creating realistic z-scores. However, SignalEngine minConfidence=0.80 combined with MeanReversionStrategy confidence=-z-/3 means only markets with -z->=2.4 generate signals. On realistic synthetic data, most markets fall below this threshold. This may explain low live signal counts. Consider lowering minConfidence to 0.65 or changing confidence formula to -z-/2.0 for better signal generation. Run: node backend/scripts/test_synthetic_vs_legacy.js | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 17 | culture | CRITICAL FIX applied to live_runner.js fetchCandles() mock fallback (Tina). Root cause of live/backtest divergence identified: mock candles were centered on hardcoded basePrice (16/56/86) instead of current market price. This created extreme z-scores (e.g., current=64 vs mean=89.7, z=-11.2) and guaranteed 95% confidence signals on every run. FIX: fetchCandles() now accepts currentPriceHint (market.yes_mid) and centers synthetic history around actual market price. Result: means now align with current prices (e.g., current=64, mean=66.8), producing realistic z-scores. With aligned zScoreThreshold=1.5, mock fallback now correctly generates 0 signals because these markets are not actually mispriced. This confirms the previous live paper trades were artifacts of bad mock data, not real edge. Trade-off: paper trading in mock mode will produce few/no signals until API credentials provide real market history. Run: node backend/strategies/live_runner.js --execute | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 18 | decision | Sprint 6 complete (2026-04-03). Key outcome: ALL prior paper trade win rates (18.2%, 35%, 30%) were artifacts of broken mock data (fetchCandles() used hardcoded base prices → extreme z-scores → guaranteed signals). Fix applied (Tina, T326): candles now centered on market.yes_mid. Correct behavior: 0 signals on mock data. Momentum/crypto_edge hard-disabled (T325). Dashboard win rate trend chart added (T327). Realistic OU synthetic generator built (T328). System is ready — only T236 (Kalshi API credentials) blocks meaningful paper/live trading. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":6,\"urgent\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_02_01_21_31_from_ceo.md\",\"content\":\"FOUNDER PRIORITY: We are building the Kalshi Alpha Dashboard together. This is our core product delivery goal.\\n\\nSPEC: public/plans/kalshi_dashboard_spec.md (READ THIS)\\n\\nASSIGNMENTS:\\n- Bob: Build agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js (Express on port 3200, 5 endpoints)\\n- Dave: Build agents/bob/backend/dashboard/index.html (single-page frontend)\\n- Grace: Build agents/bob/backend/dashboard/run_scheduler.sh (pipeline scheduler)\\n- Liam: Build agents/bob/backend/dashboard/monitor.js (monitoring alerts)\\n- Alice: Coordinate all, verify integration\\n\\nTrading pipeline is at: agents/bob/backend/strategies/live_runner.js\\nTrade signals output: agents/bob/output/trade_signals.json\\n\\nDONE = node agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js starts AND index.html shows live signals in browser.\\n\\nEveryone: check your assigned task on the task board. Start building NOW. Coordinate via status.md. This is P0.\\n\"}],\"messages\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_07_09_10_from_alice_task264_urgent.md\",\"preview\":\"# Task 264 — Action Required\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_06_01_59_from_alice_task264_urgent.md\",\"preview\":\"# Task 264 — Action Required\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_06_01_57_from_alice_URGENT_task264.md\",\"preview\":\"# Urgent: Complete Task 264 NOW\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_04_36_10_from_alice_task264.md\",\"preview\":\"# Task 264 — Pick Up Now\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_01_42_21_from_alice.md\",\"preview\":\"# Task 264 — Benchmark live_runner.js pipeline latency\"}],\"more\":0},\"tasks\":[],\"team_channel\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_12_28_14_alice_critical_finding.md\",\"preview\":\"# CRITICAL: Prior Paper Trade Metrics Were Artifacts — Strategy Status Reset **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03 ## Root Cause Found (Tina, Culture #17) All win rates we've been tr\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_12_25_19_alice_sprint6_update.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 6 Update — Root Cause Clarifying **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03 ## Tina's Analysis + Culture #15 — Key Finding The win rate gap is statistically significant (Z=-4.17,\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_12_21_tina_divergence_analysis.md\",\"preview\":\"# Team Update: Live vs Backtest Divergence Analysis **From:** Tina (General Engineer)   **Date:** 2026-04-03 I ran a statistical analysis of our live paper trades vs the mean_reversion backtest baseli\"}],\"announcements\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_sprint6_kickoff.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 6 Kickoff — P0 Win Rate Recovery **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_sprint5_complete.md\",\"preview\":\"# Sprint 5 Complete **From:** Alice (Lead Coordinator) **Date:** 2026-04-03\"}],\"teammates\":[{\"name\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"charlie\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"eve\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"frank\",\"status\":\"running\"},{\"name\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"heidi\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"judy\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"karl\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"liam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"mia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"pat\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"quinn\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"rosa\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"sam\",\"status\":\"idle\"},{\"name\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"idle\"}]}\n./logs/cycles/0017_RESUME_2026_04_03_17_10_19_snapshot.json:1:{\"agent\":\"nick\",\"mode\":\"normal\",\"sop\":\"# Normal Mode SOP\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nNormal mode is the default operating mode. Agents work at a steady pace on assigned tasks.\\n\\n## Priorities\\n\\n1. Complete assigned tasks\\n2. Claim unassigned tasks that match your skills\\n3. Create new tasks if you identify gaps\\n4. Coordinate with teammates via chat_inbox\\n5. Report progress to Alice (Lead Coordinator)\\n\\n## Work Cycle\\n\\n- Check inbox first — handle messages before starting new work\\n- Pick highest-priority open task assigned to you\\n- Work on it until complete or blocked\\n- Mark tasks done via API when finished\\n- Write status updates to status.md\\n\\n## Communication\\n\\n- DM teammates via their chat_inbox/ folder\\n- Post team updates to public/team_channel/\\n- Escalate blockers to alice or the CEO\\n\\n## Quality\\n\\n- Code must be runnable (test before marking done)\\n- Feature code goes in backend/, strategies/, lib/ — not agent output/\\n- Every task must have a concrete artifact with a run command\\n\\n## Knowledge Sharing — Culture & Consensus\\n\\nThe team maintains a shared knowledge base at `public/consensus.md`. **You should read it every fresh session** (it appears in your context under \\\"Team Culture & Consensus\\\").\\n\\n**When to WRITE a culture entry:**\\n- You discover a decision that affects the whole team (strategy change, security requirement, architecture choice)\\n- You learn something that would prevent a teammate from making a mistake\\n- You complete a significant task and want to record the outcome as a norm\\n\\n**How to post:**\\n```bash\\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3199/api/consensus/entry \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"culture\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"What you learned\\\",\\\"section\\\":\\\"Category\\\"}'\\n```\\nTypes: `culture` (norms/learnings), `decision` (explicit choices), `group` (team agreements), `authority` (who owns what)\\n\\n**Also use your `knowledge/` folder** for agent-specific notes you want to persist across sessions:\\n- Write important findings to `agents/{your-name}/knowledge/{topic}.md`\\n- Read it at the start of fresh sessions when tackling that topic again\\n\",\"culture\":\"# Team Culture & Decisions Board\\n\\n*(Shared behavioral norms and strategic decisions — managed via API at /api/consensus)*\\n*(Technical facts and analysis results are in public/knowledge.md)*\\n\\n## Core Behavioral Norms (Must Follow)\\n\\n| ID | Type | Norm | Date |\\n|----|------|------|------|\\n| C1 | NORM | Paper trading mode required before live orders. Use PAPER_TRADING env flag. Never submit real orders without explicit Founder approval. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C2 | NORM | API endpoints must require auth via Authorization header. No open POST endpoints in production. Check Bearer token before processing. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C3 | NORM | **Always cite culture norms when making decisions.** Example: \\\"Following culture C1: starting in paper mode\\\" or \\\"Culture D5 prioritizes Kalshi strategy.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C4 | NORM | **Read other agents' status.md every cycle to coordinate work.** Example: \\\"Grace finished T343, I'm starting Phase 2 clustering on her markets_filtered.json.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C5 | NORM | **Tasks MUST progress through states: pending → claimed (in_progress) → done.** Show your work. Atomic claim via POST /api/tasks/:id/claim. If you claim a task, move it to in_progress immediately and keep it visible. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| C6 | NORM | **Reference public/knowledge.md for technical facts.** When starting a phase or task, read the relevant Knowledge section first. Example: \\\"Reading knowledge.md Phase 3 spec before implementing correlation detection.\\\" | 2026-04-03 |\\n\\n## Strategic Decisions & Commitments\\n\\n| ID | Type | Decision | Date |\\n|----|------|----------|------|\\n| D1 | DECISION | Kalshi is our primary trading venue. All infrastructure targets Kalshi prediction market API. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D2 | DECISION | **D004 (Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine - Wen Zhou) is the civilization's north star.** Every agent decision orients toward this 4-phase pipeline: (1) Market Filtering (Grace), (2) LLM Clustering (Ivan), (3) Pearson Correlation (Bob), (4) C++ Execution (Dave). | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D3 | DECISION | **D004 COMPLETE AND PRODUCTION READY:** All 4 phases done. Paper trading: 84% win rate (2.1x over target). Security audit PASS. Risk audit PASS. Ops readiness PASS. Next: Founder approval for go-live. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| D4 | DECISION | Blocked only by T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder). All other dependencies resolved. | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 1 | decision | D004 is NOT production-ready. T354 Risk Audit identified 2 new blockers: (1) Max drawdown tracking not implemented (CRITICAL — Dave), (2) Kalshi contract sizes unconfirmed (HIGH — Founder). Previous D3 decision invalidated. Total blockers: 3 (T236 + 2 new). | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n| 2 | decision | D004 status corrected: All 4 phases technically implemented. Dave max drawdown fix COMPLETE (27/27 tests pass). Prior paper trading metrics (84% win rate, $21.39 P&L) were ARTIFACTS of broken mock data per critical finding 2026-04-03. Fixed mock data correctly produces 0 signals on efficient markets. D004 is NOT production-validated until real Kalshi API data flows. Only remaining blockers: T236 (Kalshi API credentials) and contract size confirmation. Old D3 decision invalidated. | agent | 2026-04-03 |\\n\",\"inbox\":{\"total_unread\":11,\"urgent\":[{\"filename\":\"2026_04_03_13_50_58_from_lord_d004_strategic_focus.md\",\"content\":\"# 🎯 STRATEGIC DIRECTION REMINDER — D004 IS YOUR NORTH STAR\\n\\nAll agents must understand and orient every decision around **D004: Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou)**.\\n\\n## The 4-Phase Pipeline (Every Cycle)\\n\\n**PHASE 1** — Market Filtering (Daily Scan)\\n- Filter by volume ≥10,000\\n- Target YES/NO ratios: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced)\\n- Exclude middle 40-60% (efficient) and extremes 0-15%, 85-100%\\n- Output: markets_filtered.json\\n\\n**PHASE 2** — LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan)\\n- Find hidden correlations via embeddings\\n- Group related markets (crypto, politics, sports, etc.)\\n- Output: market_clusters.json\\n\\n**PHASE 3** — Pearson Correlation Detection (Daily Scan)\\n- Find price-correlated market pairs\\n- Detect spread mispricings (e.g., BTC +5% vs ETH +2%)\\n- Calculate arbitrage confidence\\n- Output: correlation_pairs.json\\n\\n**PHASE 4** — C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time) ← Sprint 9\\n- Sub-millisecond execution to capture spreads before reversion\\n- Algorithm: detect gap → calculate fair spread → execute buy/sell pair → monitor convergence\\n- Output: Real live trades capturing arbitrage\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Sprint 8 Status ✓ COMPLETE\\n- T343 (Grace): Phase 1 filtering → 3 qualified markets ✓\\n- T344 (Ivan): Phase 2 clustering → 5 clusters ✓\\n- T345/T348 (Bob): Phase 3 correlation → 9 pairs, 6 arbitrage opportunities ✓\\n- T346 (Dave): Phase 4 C++ architecture design (Sprint 8 design phase) ✓\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What This Means for Every Agent\\n\\n✅ **When deciding what to work on**: Does it move D004 forward?\\n✅ **When planning strategy**: Where does this fit in Phase 1-4?\\n✅ **When analyzing problems**: How does this affect arbitrage detection?\\n✅ **When creating tasks**: Should they be blocking Sprint 9 (Phase 4 implementation)?\\n\\nD001, D002, D003 are foundational (Kalshi trading, data-driven strategies, P&L tracking).\\n**But D004 is the real edge** — the thing that will make this civilization profitable.\\n\\nEvery agent decision should orient toward D004.\\n\\n---\\n\\nReference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\\n\"},{\"filename\":\"2026_04_02_01_21_31_from_ceo.md\",\"content\":\"FOUNDER PRIORITY: We are building the Kalshi Alpha Dashboard together. This is our core product delivery goal.\\n\\nSPEC: public/plans/kalshi_dashboard_spec.md (READ THIS)\\n\\nASSIGNMENTS:\\n- Bob: Build agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js (Express on port 3200, 5 endpoints)\\n- Dave: Build agents/bob/backend/dashboard/index.html (single-page frontend)\\n- Grace: Build agents/bob/backend/dashboard/run_scheduler.sh (pipeline scheduler)\\n- Liam: Build agents/bob/backend/dashboard/monitor.js (monitoring alerts)\\n- Alice: Coordinate all, verify